reviews.review_text: Excellent perspective from this source. Thank you.   This is a great listen.   Thanks for your efforts and all the details you left us with in your write-up.   Happy New Years.

nice and mellow notes to self: unique edit...vocals sound cool and different... easy on my ears... shakedown is bumpy and long (nice) ... big boss man got a nice feel to it (sloppy & bluesy harmonica work) ...best stuff is in 2nd set ... listen to this when I want great music for some mindless task I have to do ... the whole 2nd set flows from song to song like I like (note: forget that Ken Keysey crap next time I listen to it)

Holy crap!  1981 Dark Star! Wow.  Amazing sounding, amazingly played, PERFECT!

Mr. Serafin, thank you so so so much for your hard work with this!  Your notes please me almost as much as the Dark Star, the Shakedown, the PITB->Terrapin->PITB, and the Morning Dew.

What a find!  Thanks again....

Thank you! I am always a matrix kinda of audiophile and generally dislikes boards because of the lack of audience presence. But this mix and the annotations have shifted my snobbery quite a bit.
-Peace
2nd set gem great sound and great, moving 2nd set - -setlist speaks for itself
